docs/index.rst
     1Ôćĺ``pluggy``
     2Ôćĺ==========
     3Ôćĺ**The pytest plugin system**
     4Ôćĺ
     5ÔćĺWhat is it?
     6Ôćĺ***********
     7Ôćĺ``pluggy`` is the crystallized core of :ref:`plugin management and hook
     8Ôćĺcalling <pytest:writing-plugins>` for :std:doc:`pytest <pytest:index>`.
     9ÔćĺIt enables `1400+ plugins`_ to extend and customize ``pytest``'s default
    10Ôćĺbehaviour. Even ``pytest`` itself is composed as a set of ``pluggy`` plugins
    11Ôćĺwhich are invoked in sequence according to a well defined set of protocols.
    12Ôćĺ
    13ÔćĺIt gives users the ability to extend or modify the behaviour of a
    14Ôćĺ``host program`` by installing a ``plugin`` for that program.
    15ÔćĺThe plugin code will run as part of normal program execution, changing or
    16Ôćĺenhancing certain aspects of it.
    17Ôćĺ
    18ÔćĺIn essence, ``pluggy`` enables function `hooking`_ so you can build
    19Ôćĺ"pluggable" systems.
    20Ôćĺ
    21ÔćĺWhy is it useful?
    22Ôćĺ*****************
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ


